# Tire Service Landing — Cursor Rules

## Strict Rules

- **Semantic HTML5:** Use `<header>`, `<section>`, `<nav>`, `<footer>`, `<article>` and other semantic tags. No div-soup.
- **Accessibility (a11y) is critical:** Add `alt` on every `<img>`. Use `aria-label` / `aria-labelledby` where it improves context (nav, buttons, sections).
- **No inline styles.** Use classes and external CSS only. All presentation in `css/styles.css`.
- **CSS Variables** for colors and fonts. Define in `:root`, use throughout.
- **Layout:** Use Flexbox and CSS Grid. Do not use `float` for layout.
- **Mobile-First:** Default styles are for mobile. Use `@media (min-width: ...)` to add or override for tablet/desktop. Do not use desktop-first or max-width as primary approach.
- **Reset CSS** — required at the top of main CSS:
  ```css
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }
  ```

## HTML/CSS Best Practices

### HTML
- Use meaningful `id` and `class` names (BEM notation recommended: `.block__element--modifier`)
- Every interactive element must have minimum touch target size of 44x44px
- Forms must have proper `<label>` association with inputs via `for` attribute or nesting
- Use `<button type="button">` for non-submit actions, `<button type="submit">` for forms
- Always specify `lang` attribute on `<html>` tag (e.g., `lang="ru"`)
- Meta viewport tag is mandatory: `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">`

### CSS
- **Spacing System:** Use consistent spacing scale via CSS variables (`--spacing-*` or `--space-*`)
- **Typography Scale:** Define font sizes as CSS variables (e.g., `--font-size-sm`, `--font-size-base`, `--font-size-lg`)
- **Color Contrast:** Ensure WCAG AA compliance minimum (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)
- **Avoid magic numbers:** Use named CSS variables instead of hardcoded values
- **Use `rem` for font sizes** and spacing where appropriate for better accessibility
- **Avoid `!important`** unless absolutely necessary (e.g., utility classes)
- **Group related properties:** positioning → box model → typography → visual → misc
- **Prefer shorthand properties** where it improves readability (e.g., `margin`, `padding`, `border`)
- **Transitions:** Define reusable transition values as CSS variables (e.g., `--transition-fast: 0.15s ease`)

### Performance
- Minimize CSS selectors depth (max 3 levels recommended)
- Use `will-change` sparingly and only when needed
- Prefer `transform` and `opacity` for animations (GPU-accelerated)
- Load web fonts with `font-display: swap` to prevent FOIT (Flash of Invisible Text)
- Optimize images: use WebP format where supported, provide proper `width` and `height` attributes

### Naming Conventions
- **Classes:** Use lowercase with hyphens (`.header-navigation`)
- **CSS Variables:** Use descriptive names with prefixes (`--color-primary`, `--spacing-md`)
- **IDs:** Use sparingly, only for unique landmark elements or JS hooks

## Project Context

- Pure HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JS. No build tools, no frameworks.
- Static site: open `index.html` in browser or serve via any static server.
- Images in `assets/images/`. Reference with relative paths.
- Language: Russian (ru)
